Representative John Lewis expresses his support for President Obama's Jobs Speech, describing it as bold, thoughtful, and inspiring. He believes that the proposed American Jobs Act can help resolve the country's problems, despite concerns about its cost. Lewis emphasizes the importance of everyone paying their fair share and reforming government where necessary. He also urges Congress to make hard choices and compromises for the benefit of the American people, putting aside partisanship. Lewis is pleased that the President plans to reach out to the American people for support and believes that with the backing of Congress and the business community, Obama can successfully re-energize and rebuild the economy.